   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "Based on the exploratory analysis of the Bengaluru Zomato dataset, several interesting patterns were identified. Quick Bites and Casual Dining restaurants dominate the restaurant market, indicating a strong preference for convenient and affordable dining options. Online ordering services have been widely adopted, with a significant proportion of restaurants offering delivery facilities through the platform.\n",
    "\n",
    "The analysis also revealed that table booking services are available in only a small number of restaurants, suggesting that most establishments primarily cater to casual dining customers. Restaurants offering table booking facilities generally tend to be more expensive than those without such services.\n",
    "\n",
    "Restaurant ratings were found to be largely concentrated between 3 and 4, indicating that most restaurants receive generally positive customer feedback. While restaurant cost and ratings show a positive relationship, the correlation is moderate, suggesting that higher prices do not necessarily guarantee better ratings.\n",
    "\n",
    "Location and cuisine also play an important role in restaurant pricing and popularity. Affordable restaurants are available across most areas of Bengaluru, while premium restaurants are concentrated in selected locations. Furthermore, a small number of cuisines dominate the market, reflecting the dining preferences of customers in the city.\n",
    "\n",
